Key Development Question
How can I strengthen my technical leadership and increase my involvement in architectural decisions while remaining deeply hands-on and leveraging emerging technologies to improve engineering effectiveness?
Behaviors and Skills
Increase participation in architectural discussions and technical decision-making.
Continue developing technical leadership through ownership, mentoring, and knowledge sharing.
Strengthen communication and collaboration with engineers and stakeholders beyond the immediate team.
Identify practical opportunities to leverage AI and emerging technologies to improve engineering productivity and software delivery.
Continue building expertise in solving complex technical and system design challenges.
What support do I need from my Manager?
Provide opportunities to participate in larger technical initiatives and design discussions.
Offer regular feedback on technical leadership and areas for growth.
Encourage exposure to projects and collaborations beyond the immediate team when appropriate.
Support continuous learning and experimentation with AI and emerging technologies.
Help increase visibility of my contributions and create opportunities to expand my impact.
What success measures will signal progress on your Key Development Question (KDQ)?
Increased ownership of larger initiatives from design through production delivery.
More involvement in architectural discussions and technical decision-making.
Positive feedback from peers, stakeholders, and leadership regarding technical contributions and collaboration.
Recognition as a trusted engineer for solving complex technical challenges.
Continued mentoring and knowledge sharing that strengthen team capability.
Successful application of AI and emerging technologies to improve engineering productivity and software quality.
Increased collaboration beyond the immediate team when opportunities arise.